        <ul>
          <li>Astrocytic receptors can detect nearby synaptic activity and trigger intracellular signaling</li>
          <li>Astrocyte activation can release Ca2+ from internal stores before membrane-level feedback occurs</li>
          <li>After that delayed Ca2+ response, gliotransmitters are released into the extracellular space and can bind nearby neuronal GPCRs</li>
          <li>This illustrates bidirectional neuron-glia communication within a tripartite synapse</li>
        </ul>

